answers.answer: Mine raised slightly around then too. 130/90. They didn't seem too concerned. How high was yours?
Mine was also 130/90. It's never been high before my appointment yesterday. I think he's concerned due to the protein in my urine.
I've had protein in my urine alot, they would only be concerned if it's accompanied with high blood pressure! If it was just protein you'd be fine! :-)

question: hello everyone!! I went in for my 38 week appointment yesterday and was told I had protein in my urine and my blood pressure was high. This is the first time my blood pressure has ever been high. He sent me home with a jug to pee in for 24 hours and I have to take it back this afternoon to confirm if I have it. I'm just wondering what will happen if I do? He said he'd induce me but I was wondering how they'd monitor me differently? Or if anyone thought they had it and they don't?
title: Preeclampsia
